Sounds like the "plan" was working great. Windows was supposed to be used to
boost interest in OS/2, right? Well, Windows started to sell at 3.0, but
Microsoft decided they didn't want to follow through with their promises for
the second part of that statement and thus dumped their OS/2 customers.

>>You keep mentioning that OS/2 2.0 was half and half 16/32 bit. Do you
